系統識別號
U0026-0812200915144962


論文名稱(中文) 
      
台灣TFT-LCD企業經營策略、競爭優勢與績效之比較研究


論文名稱(英文) 
      
A Study on the Relationship Between Business Strategy,and Competitive Advantage and Operating Performance of Taiwan's TFT-LCD Industry


校院名稱
成功大學


系所名稱(中)
高階管理碩士在職專班(EMBA)


系所名稱(英)
Executive Master of Business Administration (EMBA)


學年度
97


學期
2


出版年
98


研究生(中文)
翁姿芳


學號
R0796131


學位類別
碩士


語文別
中文


口試日期
2009-06-11


論文頁數
142頁


口試委員
口試委員-康信鴻
指導教授-莊雙喜
口試委員-蔡明田



關鍵字(中)
經營策略企業績效競爭優勢


關鍵字(英)
Competitive AdvantageBusiness StrategyOperating PerformanceTFT-LCD


學科別分類



中文摘要
TFT-LCD產業為全球新興高科技產業，此產業結合台灣既有的電子產品製造優勢及政府與民間企業的大力投入，已具備有領先世界的潛力；因此TFT-LCD產業更成為台灣經濟發展的核心目標。面板產業最重要的就是整個供應鏈的管理。近來，臺南科學園區與中部科學園區的相繼成立，其中的光電產業群聚，企業之間形成群聚，產業便可藉由內在動力自我發展，建構與彈性調整，進而提升整體產業的競爭力。 本研究針對台灣TFT-LCD面板產業進行分析，以個案研究方法探討產業中主要廠商的經營策略。選擇友達光電、奇美電子、群創光電為研究對象，分析廠商在台灣的產業環境中，如何運用其所擁有的資源，來達到策略目標。並對其策略執行結果進行歸納與分析。經由上述分析研究，目的在於找出產業中能夠成功經營的策略，並期望能提供TFT-LCD面板廠商，在未來制定與執行策略時的參考依據。研究結果發現，台灣廠商之主要競爭優勢在於彈性之製造管理能力及良好之市場行銷通路，積極進行垂直策略聯盟以尋求與供應商及銷售通路間的垂直連結，使得相關的價值活動達到最佳化，以強化企業之競爭優勢。因此業者必須掌握企業核心競爭力、認清液晶循環趨勢及擬定企業競爭策略;進而尋求企業合併與上中下游產業的垂直整合;並且建議政府提供穩定的投資環境與提昇廠商研發能力，藉以在TFT-LCD產業中取得持續性的競爭優勢。


英文摘要
AbstractThe TFT-LCD industry is Taiwan’s newly developing high-tech industry. This potentially world leading industry combines Taiwan’s electronics production advantages with developmental support from both government and business. Thus the TFT-LCD industry became a major target goal for economic development in Taiwan. Supply-chain management is very important in the TFT-LCD industry. The optoelectronics clustering in the more recently established Tainan Science-based Industrial Park, as well as in the Central Taiwan Science Park have laid down a solid production (manufacturing) foundation. When companies form a cluster, the aim is to reach a “critical mass” that enables the relevant industry to develop via the inner strength of the cluster, to build and adjust flexibly, and thereby to enhance its overall competitiveness. This research analyzed the TFT-LCD panel industry in Taiwan, and investigated the main manufacturers' business strategy through a case study. AUO, CMO, and InnoLux were chosen as the case targets. The purpose of this study was to discover the strategy which best supports the TFT-LCD panel industry. The means by which the companies utilized the resources of each manufacturer to reach strategy objectives are discussed. The study also makes an inference and analysis from the results, and provides suggestions for implementing and practicing the strategy for the future manufacturers of TFT-LCD panels. Results indicate that two main competitive advantages of Taiwan’s TFT-LCD firms: flexible manufacturing capability and excellent marketing channels. Most firms in Taiwan are vertically allied with suppliers and market channels to optimize every value activity that enhances the company’s competitive advantages. Therefore these firms must maintain core competencies, predict future trends in the crystal cycle and exercise decision making in competitive strategies. In addition, industrial merging and vertical integration in linking upstream, midstream, downstream sectors, are actively searched for. It is suggested that our government should provide a steady investment environment and continue to elevate the R&D capacity of the local firms in order to obtain maintainable competitive advantage in the TFT-LCD industry.


